 Burgersdorp - A successful combined intelligence driven operation by members of Crime Intelligence, the COCC Team and Burgersdorp Vispol and reservists resulted in the arrest of three suspects for alleged drug dealing on Sunday evening at 22:00. "Positive information was followed up on at a house in Thembisa locality," described police spokesperson, Capt Ursula Roelofse. "On searching the house, the drugs were found in a panel of the electric stove in the kitchen." She said that 195 Mandrax tablets and 56 crystal meth straws with an estimated street value of R22 300 together with cash was seized. "Three suspects age 23, 22 and 22 were arrested." Acting SAPS Cluster Commander, Col Mpho Rabela, commended the combined forces on the successfull arrest and recovery of drugs. "The dealing in drugs will not be tolerated in our small towns destroying our communities," he said. "Thank you to the community for the positive information and taking the SAPS hand in the fight against crime together we will turn the tide against the criminals." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 